{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8ccb5c0a-f2de-43fa-91d7-bfb4c0ee7eb0","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by issue #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by issue #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by issue #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by issue #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** xUnit has no separate skip attribute — the `Skip` property is built into `[Fact]` / `[Theory]`. All four frameworks will report skipped tests distinctly from passed/failed in test results.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"691d998a-54f5-4961-9922-9b5d74989496","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":327,"requestId":"67CF:1F50C6:16B2E0F:197C4CD:69FD3A12"},"id":"eeb865ed-eed2-47cf-b548-6ee2ff88f2ca","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:19:21.459Z","parentId":"ce87179e-b221-4375-86b9-cd0c87ce51be"}
